data.value:
GUIDELINES:
1. The attendance shall be accomplished daily. Refer to the codes for checking learners' attendance.
2. Dates shall be written in the preceeding columns beside Learners' Name.
3. To compute the following: a. Percentage of Enrollment = Registered Learner as of End of the Month --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- x 100 Enrollment as of 1st Friday of June
b. Average Daily Attendance = Total Daily Attendance ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- x 100 Number of School Days in reporting month
c. Percentage of Attendance for the month = Average daily attendance ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- x 100 Registered Learner as of End of the Month
4. Every End of the month, the class adviser willsubmit this form to the principal for recording of summary table into the School Form 4. Once signed by the principal, this form should be returned to the adviser.
5. The adviser will extend necessary intervention including but not limited to home visitation to learner/s that commited 5 consecutive days of absences or those with potentials of dropping out.
6. Attendance performance of learner is expected to reflect in Form 137 and Form 138 every grading period * Beginning ofSchool Year cut-off report is every 1st day of School Calendar Days.
